The most common sensitive materials in typical temperature sensors are Pt and Au. Bin et al. [6] used the Micro-Electro-Mechanical System (MEMS) technology and proposed platinum as the sensing material deposited on the PI film after a peeling process. After lamination forming the required pattern, it is used to monitor the temperature change of 20–120 °C, and the TCR value is 0.0032∘C-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
